[2;36m                    [0m         # Evaluation Report                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Summary                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         A Jazzer-based fuzzing run has uncovered a critical OS command injection            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         vulnerability in the code path exercised by the HTML parser harness. The sanitizer  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `OsCommandInjection.processImplStartHook` triggered when `[1;35mProcessBuilder.start[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m`   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1m([0mand by extension `Runtime.exec`[1m)[0m was invoked with potentially attacker-controlled  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         data. This behavior can lead to arbitrary command execution on the host.            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Description                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Issue Identification                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           The crash report raised a                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `com.code_intelligence.jazzer.api.FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical: OS Command           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Injection`, indicating that untrusted input is reaching an operating-system command [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         invocation.                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Vulnerability Type                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           OS Command Injection: attacker-controlled data is used in the construction or     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         execution of a system command, enabling remote code execution.                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Key Observations                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           • The sanitizer hook at                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `[1;35mOsCommandInjection.processImplStartHook[0m[1m([0mOsCommandInjection.jav[1;92ma:63[0m[1m)[0m` flagged the   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         call to `[1;35mProcessBuilder.start[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m`.                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           • The stack trace shows `[1;35mProcessBuilder.start[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` and `[1;35mRuntime.exec[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` being       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         invoked from `org.apache.tika.parser.external.ExternalParser.parse` [1m([0mlines [1;36m274[0m and  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m314[0m[1m)[0m.                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           • The fuzzer harness [1m([0m`com.example.HtmlParserFuzzer`[1m)[0m drives the parsing via      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `[1;35mparseOne[0m[1m([0m[33m...[0m[1m)[0m` and `[1;35mfuzzerTestOneInput[0m[1m([0m[33m...[0m[1m)[0m`, but the harness merely exposes the   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         underlying parser routines—it is not the root cause.                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Affected Code Areas for Holistic Review                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           [1;36m1[0m. **ExternalParser Class**                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              – Methods around line [1;36m274[0m and [1;36m314[0m where external processes are launched.       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              – Construction of command-line arguments passed to `ProcessBuilder` or         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `Runtime.exec`.                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           [1;36m2[0m. **OsCommandInjection Sanitizer**                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              – The hook implementation in `OsCommandInjection.processImplStartHook` to      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         understand which patterns or conditions were flagged.                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           [1;36m3[0m. **HTML Parsing Pipeline**                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              – `HtmlHandler.handleDataURIScheme` and related data-URI processing in         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `HtmlHandler` [1m([0mHtmlHandler.jav[1;92ma:377[0m[1m)[0m.                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              – Successive parser decorators and composite parsers [1m([0m`ParserDecorator`,       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `CompositeParser`, `AutoDetectParser`, `DelegatingParser`[1m)[0m.                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           [1;36m4[0m. **Fuzzer Harness Code**                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              – Entry points in `HtmlParserFuzzer.jav[1;92ma:40[0m` [1m([0m`fuzzerTestOneInput`[1m)[0m and        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `HtmlParserFuzzer.jav[1;92ma:69[0m` [1m([0m`parseOne`[1m)[0m.                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              – While not root cause, understanding how inputs are fed into the parser may   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         aid in reproducing and triaging the issue.                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         This information should guide further investigation into how external commands are  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         constructed and executed within the parsing framework, and which inputs flow into   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         those command invocations.                                                          [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m414[0m[39m:        CompositeExternalParser exParser =[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m415[0m[39m:                [0m[1;39m([0m[39mCompositeExternalParser[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mEmbeddedDocumentUtil.tryToFindExistingLeafParser[0m[1;39m([0m[39mCompositeExternalParser.class,[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m416[0m[39m:                        context[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m417[0m[39m:        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mexParser == null[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m418[0m[39m:            return;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m419[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m420[0m[39m:        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39madded == [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtika-core/src/main/java/org/apache/tika/parser/external/ExternalParser.jav[0m[1;92ma:308[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m315[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m308[0m[39m:        [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Execute[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m309[0m[39m:        Process process = null;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m310[0m[39m:        try [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m311[0m[39m:            if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmd.length == [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m312[0m[39m:                process = [0m[1;35mRuntime.getRuntime[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.exec[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmd[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m313[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m314[0m[39m:                process = [0m[1;35mRuntime.getRuntime[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.exec[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmd[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m315[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Root Cause Analysis Summary[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The OS command injection arises because ExternalParser uses [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mRuntime.getRuntime[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.exec[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m when the configured command line consists of a [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msingle element. The [0m[1;35mexec[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m overload delegates to a shell-like interpretation [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mon the command string, allowing attacker-controlled tokens [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., temporary file [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpaths derived from untrusted HTML data URIs[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to inject extra commands or arguments.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - By contrast, the [0m[1;35mexec[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m[39m overload or using ProcessBuilder with a [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mString[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m argument invokes the executable directly with each array element treated [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mas a discrete argument, preventing shell metacharacter interpretation.[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The vulnerability manifests in tika-core’s `[0m[1;35mExternalParser.parse[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39maround lines [0m[1;36m311[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m315[0m[39m, where:[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       ```[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmd.length == [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           process = [0m[1;35mRuntime.getRuntime[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.exec[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmd[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;    [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m vulnerable[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           process = [0m[1;35mRuntime.getRuntime[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.exec[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmd[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;       [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m safer[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       ```[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - A similar pattern exists in the external2 variant, but that one already uses [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`new [0m[1;35mProcessBuilder[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmdList[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.start[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, which is safe.[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Fix Strategy Overview[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Eliminate any usage of [0m[1;35mRuntime.exec[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m with a single command string.[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Unify the ExternalParser implementations to always invoke external processes [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvia the [0m[1;35mexec[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m[39m overload or, preferably, via [0m[1;35mProcessBuilder[0m[1;39m([0m[39mList<String>[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Ensure that the sequence of tokens [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthe command and its arguments[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is passed [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexactly as discrete elements, so no shell parsing occurs.[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Preserve existing placeholder substitution logic and all downstream stream [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhandling.[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Do **not** modify harness code, tests, or external dependencies.[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Implementation Steps[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   A. Modify tika-core’s ExternalParser [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39msrc/main/java/org/apache/tika/parser/external/ExternalParser.java[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. Locate the block around lines [0m[1;36m308[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m315[0m[39m:[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ```[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Execute[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         Process process = null;[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         try [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmd.length == [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                 process = [0m[1;35mRuntime.getRuntime[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.exec[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmd[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                 process = [0m[1;35mRuntime.getRuntime[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.exec[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmd[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m catch [0m[1;39m([0m[39mException e[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[1;35mLOG.warn[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"problem with process exec"[0m[39m, e[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ```[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. Replace it with a single code path that uses ProcessBuilder:[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ```[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Execute safely without shell interpretation[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         Process process;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         try [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             process = new [0m[1;35mProcessBuilder[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmd[0m[1;39m)[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                            [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Optionally: inherit environment and working [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdirectory as before[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                            [0m[1;35m.redirectErrorStream[0m[1;39m([0m[39mfalse[0m[1;39m)[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                            [0m[1;35m.start[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m catch [0m[1;39m([0m[39mIOException e[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[1;35mLOG.warn[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"problem starting external process"[0m[39m, e[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             return;  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m or handle consistent with existing error path[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ```[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         - This guarantees each `cmd[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mi[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` is treated as a separate argument.[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         - `[0m[1;35mredirectErrorStream[0m[1;39m([0m[39mfalse[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` preserves separate stdout/stderr streams as[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbefore.[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. Remove the `cmd.length == [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m` check entirely.[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. Ensure `cmd` is never empty; if it is, the existing initialization [0m[35m/[0m[39m [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconfig checks will catch it.[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   B. [0m[1;39m([0m[39mOptional[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m For consistency, verify that the external2 package’s [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mExternalParser path always uses ProcessBuilder. If any [0m[1;35mexec[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m calls exist, [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrefactor them similarly.[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   C. Add a small unit test [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor augment an existing one[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m under tika-core’s test [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msuite to validate that commands containing spaces or shell metacharacters in the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39margument [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., a file name with `; rm -rf [0m[35m/[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m do not result in unintended extra [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprocess execution. This confirms the fix.[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Preservation of Critical Logic[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Placeholder replacement for `$[0m[1;39m{[0m[39mIN[0m[1;33mPUT[0m[39m_FILE_TOKEN[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m` and `$[0m[1;39m{[0m[39mOUT[0m[1;33mPUT[0m[39m_FILE_TOKEN[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m` [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mremains unchanged.[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All stream-handling and metadata-extraction routines after process launch [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mremain intact.[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Tests and harness logic continue to feed inputs and exercise the parsing [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpipeline without modification.[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Justification and Side-Effect Mitigation[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Using ProcessBuilder over [0m[1;35mexec[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is an established best practice to [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mavoid OS command injection [0m[1;39m([0m[39msee existing external2 implementation in [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`external2/ExternalParser`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - There is no change to the configured command-line semantics: a single-element [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcommand still invokes that executable with no arguments; a multi-element list still[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmatches previous behavior, only now without shell parsing.[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - If any user-provided commandLine entries assumed shell expansion [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwildcard expansion or shell built-ins[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, those will no longer work. However, since [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mExternalParser is intended to wrap standalone executables [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., `exiftool`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, this [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchange aligns with secure usage.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No broad exception-catchers are introduced; only IOException is handled at the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprocess start, consistent with the original approach.[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. References[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Aligns with the pattern in [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`tika-core/src/main/java/org/apache/tika/parser/external2/ExternalParser.java`, [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhich safely uses ProcessBuilder.[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Matches the security guidance from the Java documentation: prefer [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mexec[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m[39m or ProcessBuilder over [0m[1;35mexec[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to avoid shell injection [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvulnerabilities.[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcode_range: [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtika-core/src/main/java/org/apache/tika/parser/external/ExternalParser.jav[0m[1;92ma:308[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m315[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                 at                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mcom.example.HtmlParserFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput[0m[1m([0mHtmlParserFuzzer.jav[1;92ma:40[0m[1m)[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         DEDUP_TOKEN: 3c99eeb1380e104c                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         == libFuzzer crashing input ==                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mReport[0m===                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         # Evaluation Report                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Summary                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         The initial issue uncovered by Jazzer is an OS command injection vulnerability in   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `org.apache.tika.parser.external.ExternalParser`. The fuzzer reports that           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         attacker-controlled data reaches a call to `ProcessBuilder.start` [1m([0mformerly         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `Runtime.exec`[1m)[0m, allowing remote code execution.                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         A patch attempt replaced the direct `[1;35mRuntime.getRuntime[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m[1;35m.exec[0m[1m([0m[33m...[0m[1m)[0m` calls with a   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         single `new [1;35mProcessBuilder[0m[1m([0mcmd[1m)[0m[1;35m.redirectErrorStream[0m[1m([0mfalse[1m)[0m[1;35m.start[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` invocation,     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         catching `IOException` instead of the broader `Exception`. The intent was to        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         eliminate shell interpretation and unify process creation in one API.               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         After applying the patch, the fuzzer still reports the same                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical: OS Command Injection` at `ProcessBuilder.start`,      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         indicating that the use of untrusted data in the command array remains and the      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         issue is not resolved by simply switching to `ProcessBuilder`.                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Description                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Initial Issue                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - The fuzzer crash log indicates a security sanitizer hook                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1m([0m`OsCommandInjection.processImplStartHook`[1m)[0m being triggered on                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `ProcessBuilder.start`, flagging an OS command injection.                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Stack trace highlights the vulnerable calls inside `ExternalParser.parse` [1m([0mlines  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ~[1;36m274[0m and ~[1;36m314[0m[1m)[0m where external processes are spawned with commands built from        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         potentially attacker-controlled input.                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - The vulnerability arises because the `cmd` array—constructed elsewhere in         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `ExternalParser`—can contain unvalidated or unsanitized data, leading to command    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         injection when executed.                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Patch Attempt                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Removed the branching logic that called `[1;35mRuntime.getRuntime[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m[1;35m.exec[0m[1m([0mcmd[1m[[0m[1;36m0[0m[1m][0m[1m)[0m` or    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `[1;35mexec[0m[1m([0mcmd[1m)[0m` depending on the array length.                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Introduced a single `[1;35mProcessBuilder[0m[1m([0mcmd[1m)[0m[1;35m.redirectErrorStream[0m[1m([0mfalse[1m)[0m[1;35m.start[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` call [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         wrapped in a `try/catch [1m([0mIOException[1m)[0m` block, logging a warning and returning early [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         on failure.                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Updated the log message from “problem with process exec” to “problem starting     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         external process”.                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Result After Patch                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - The fuzzer still triggers `OsCommandInjection` at `ProcessBuilder.start`.         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Stack trace now points at `ExternalParser.parse` line [1;36m313[0m [1m([0mafter the patch[1m)[0m,      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         confirming that simply switching APIs does not prevent untrusted data from arriving [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         in the process builder.                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Areas for Further Investigation                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m. Construction of the `cmd` array in `ExternalParser`—identify all inputs and      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         concatenations that feed into the command.                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m. Upstream parsers [1m([0me.g., `HtmlParser`, `JSoupParser`[1m)[0m and any data                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         transformations before commands are built.                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m. Other code paths in the codebase that invoke external processes with potentially [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         untrusted arguments.                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m290[0m[39m:        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcommand.length == [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m291[0m[39m:            cmd = command[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m][0m[1;35m.split[0m[1;39m([0m[32m" "[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m292[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m293[0m[39m:            cmd = new String[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mcommand.length[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m294[0m[39m:            [0m[1;35mSystem.arraycopy[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcommand, [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, cmd, [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, command.length[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m295[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtika-core/src/main/java/org/apache/tika/parser/external2/ExternalParser.jav[0m[1;92ma:109[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m11[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m109[0m[39m:            Matcher inputMatcher = [0m[1;35mIN[0m[1;33mPUT[0m[1;35m_TOKEN_MATCHER.matcher[0m[1;39m([0m[32m""[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m110[0m[39m:            Matcher outputMatcher = [0m[1;35mOUT[0m[1;33mPUT[0m[1;35m_TOKEN_MATCHER.matcher[0m[1;39m([0m[32m""[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m111[0m[39m:            boolean outputFileInCommandline = false;[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m112[0m[39m:            for [0m[1;39m([0m[39mString c : commandLine[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m113[0m[39m:                if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35minputMatcher.reset[0m[1;39m([0m[39mc[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.find[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m114[0m[39m:                    String updated = [0m[1;35mc.replace[0m[1;39m([0m[39mIN[0m[1;33mPUT[0m[39m_FILE_TOKEN,[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m115[0m[39m:                            [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mProcessUtils.escapeCommandLine[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mp.toAbsolutePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.toString[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m116[0m[39m:                    [0m[1;35mthisCommandLine.add[0m[1;39m([0m[39mupdated[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Overview  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   The root cause of the OS command injection is that arbitrary, [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mattacker-controlled strings end up verbatim in the `cmd` array passed to [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mProcessBuilder.start[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor `Runtime.exec` in older code[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. Simply switching from [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Runtime.exec` to `ProcessBuilder` does not mitigate injection because untrusted [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstrings [0m[1;39m([0m[39mespecially in the first element, e.g. a malicious “exiftool_path” from [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHTML metadata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m can spawn a shell or invoke unexpected binaries with dangerous [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mflags.[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Key Principles  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Never execute unvalidated input.** Before spawning any external process, [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mevery element of the command array must be checked for safety.  [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Fail-safe on invalid commands.** If validation fails, the parser should [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrefuse to run the external process, logging a clear warning, and continue without [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minvoking the tool [0m[1;39m([0m[39mrather than executing a possibly malicious command[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Preserve existing functionality.** Valid workflows—canonical binaries and [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfile-path arguments—must continue to work. Tests and consumers of the old API must [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnot break under normal, safe usage.[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Detailed Steps for the Patch[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   A. In `org.apache.tika.parser.external.ExternalParser` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthe “old” external [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparser[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Locate the private `[0m[1;35mparse[0m[1;39m([0m[39mTikaInputStream…[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method around the execution point[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mlines ~[0m[1;36m308[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m316[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Introduce a new private helper method in the same class:[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```java[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     private static void [0m[1;35mvalidateCommand[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m cmd[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m throws TikaException [0m[1;39m{[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Check the executable exists and is runnable[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         Path exePath = [0m[1;35mPaths.get[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmd[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mFiles.isRegularFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mexePath[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m || ![0m[1;35mFiles.isExecutable[0m[1;39m([0m[39mexePath[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             throw new [0m[1;35mTikaException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"External executable not found or not [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32mexecutable: "[0m[39m + cmd[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m [0m[1;36m2[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Whitelist allowed characters for all args[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         for [0m[1;39m([0m[39mString arg : cmd[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Strip surrounding quotes [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfor Windows quoting[0m[1;39m)[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             String raw = arg;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mraw.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"\""[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m && [0m[1;35mraw.endsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"\""[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m && [0m[1;35mraw.length[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m > [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                 raw = [0m[1;35mraw.substring[0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m1[0m[39m, [0m[1;35mraw.length[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m - [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Allow alphanumeric, dashes, dots, slashes, backslashes and spaces[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mraw.matches[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"[0m[32m[[0m[32mA-Za-z0-9_\\-./\\\\ [0m[32m][0m[32m+"[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                 throw new [0m[1;35mTikaException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Invalid characters in command argument: "[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+ arg[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Invoke `[0m[1;35mvalidateCommand[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmd[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;` immediately before building the process—for [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mboth the old `Runtime.exec` branch [0m[1;39m([0m[39mif ever re-used[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m or the new `ProcessBuilder` [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpath.  [0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```java[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Build cmd[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m as before…[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;35mvalidateCommand[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmd[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     Process process;[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     try [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         process = new [0m[1;35mProcessBuilder[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmd[0m[1;39m)[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                     [0m[1;35m.redirectErrorStream[0m[1;39m([0m[39mfalse[0m[1;39m)[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                     [0m[1;35m.start[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     …[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - On `TikaException`, catch at the same level as `IOException` in the outer [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`parse` method, log a warning [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g. `[0m[1;35mLOG.warn[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Unsafe external command, skipping [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32mparser: [0m[32m{[0m[32m}[0m[32m"[0m[39m, [0m[1;35me.getMessage[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and return without crashing the overall parsing [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mflow.[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   B. In `org.apache.tika.parser.external2.ExternalParser` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthe “new” external2 [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mimplementation[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - After assembling `List<String> thisCommandLine` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines ~[0m[1;36m109[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m126[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m but before [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcalling `[0m[1;35mProcessUtils.execute[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, add analogous validation:[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```java[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     private static void [0m[1;35mvalidateCommandLineList[0m[1;39m([0m[39mList<String> cmdList[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m throws [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTikaException [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         String[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m cmd = [0m[1;35mcmdList.toArray[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnew String[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Reuse the same validation logic as above[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;35mvalidateCommand[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmd[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     Or copy the validation directly:[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```java[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;35mvalidateCommand[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mthisCommandLine.toArray[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnew String[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Surround the `[0m[1;35mProcessUtils.execute[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` calls with a `try [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m [0m[33m...[0m[39m [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m catch [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mTikaException te[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m [0m[1;35mLOG.warn[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Unsafe external command, skipping parser: [0m[32m{[0m[32m}[0m[32m"[0m[39m, [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mte.getMessage[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m; return; [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m` so the parser silently skips unsafe commands.[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Justification[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Prevents injection at the source.** By validating before any `[0m[1;35mstart[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, we [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mblock malicious payloads that try to spawn a shell [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[35m/bin/[0m[95msh[0m[39m -c …`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m or embed [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmetacharacters.  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Minimal API changes.** We do not alter external configuration or harness [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlogic; only augment internal safety checks.  [0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Preserves legitimate use.** Valid binaries and file paths [0m[1;39m([0m[39meven with spaces,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mafter quoting[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m match our whitelist. Flag and metadata-extraction arguments [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mpatterns, tokens[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m remain unaffected.[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Potential Side Effects & Mitigations[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Users with exotic command names or paths containing non-whitelisted symbols [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmay see their external parsers skipped. If that arises, we can expand the regex in [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuture to cover legitimately needed characters.  [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Integration tests relying on a single-string `[0m[1;35msetCommand[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"foo bar"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` being [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msplit may need minor updates; however, since we continue to support splitting, this[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mremains unchanged.  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Performance impact is negligible, as we do a single regex and file-exists [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcheck per parse invocation.[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. No Other Code Changes[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We do not modify any harness or fuzzing code.  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We do not adjust external library code or test code.  [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All existing tests for external parsers should pass; unsafe commands simply [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlog and skip rather than executing.  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m
